It emphasizes techniques such as holding the brush with actual and empty strength, applying force evenly with all five fingers; maneuvering the brush to spread ink fluidly; dotting and drawing in harmony with intent, balancing softness and sharpness uniformly; structuring characters to define form, ensuring coherence and correspondence; distributing elements intricately yet appropriately dense or sparse, allowing emptiness and fullness to coexist throughout the piece; maintaining consistent flow across the entire work.
